# "42" = Ship It

When the user sends **42** (or says "42"), treat it as a deploy request:

1. **Commit** all relevant changes (never commit `.env*`, secrets, or `data/users.json`)
2. **Push** to GitHub (`git push`)
3. **Deploy** to Vercel production: `vercel deploy --prod`

This project runs on port **3001** locally. Production is **https://mdccapitalholdings.com**. `git push` alone does not auto-deploy — always run `vercel deploy --prod` after pushing.

After `npm run build` or before confirming localhost works, follow the **dev-server** rule: kill port 3001, delete `.next`, restart `npm run dev`.
